      "title": "Split `WorkspaceRunCancelAndLoopTests.swift` into focused suites under 800 LOC",
      "description": "Principles violated: A (KISS), D (localize change), H (operational hygiene). The suite exceeds the soft file-size ceiling, making cancel/loop behavior tests harder to navigate and maintain. Why it matters: broad, monolithic test files reduce failure locality and increase maintenance overhead when evolving run-loop semantics. Minimal fix: split test groups into targeted files (cancel flow, loop completion states, retry/resume interactions) under the existing test hub pattern. Acceptance criteria: suite is decomposed into focused files and all tests continue to pass.",
